### Send multiple requests to the inventory service to trigger the circuit breaker
### Make sure the inventory-service is NOT running before executing these requests.

### Request 1 (will fail)
GET http://localhost:9000/api/inventory/1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Request 2 (will fail)
GET http://localhost:9000/api/inventory/1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Request 3 (will fail, this should trip the circuit breaker)
GET http://localhost:9000/api/inventory/1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Request 4 (should receive fallback response)
GET http://localhost:9000/api/inventory/1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

###
# Wait 5 seconds for the circuit to enter half-open state
# Then, you can test for recovery.
# Start the inventory-service and run the request below. It should succeed.

### Test recovery
GET http://localhost:9000/api/inventory/1
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}
